text: Nikki Todd, (born July 7, 1990) is a Canadian professional squash player who represents Canada. She reached a career-high world ranking of World No. 49 in April 2018.SquashInfo Player Profile In January 2018, Todd was named to Canada's 2018 Commonwealth Games team. == References == == External links == * * Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian female squash players Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for Canada Category:Pan American Games medalists in squash Category:Pan American Games silver medalists for Canada Category:Sportspeople from Regina, Saskatchewan Category:Sportspeople from Toronto Category:Squash players at the 2015 Pan American Games Category:Squash players at the 2018 Commonwealth Games
